## BP-009-VIS-01: Serve model as JSON

test TC-VIS-01-01 "GET /api/model returns the parsed model"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-01
  given: a SystemModel with components, requirements,
         interfaces, and test specs
  when: GET /api/model is requested from the running server
  expect: status 200 and a JSON body whose top-level keys
          include "components", "requirements", "interfaces",
          and "test_specs", each a list populated from the
          model

test TC-VIS-01-02 "Counts match the parsed model"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-01
  given: a SystemModel with 2 components and 3 requirements
  when: GET /api/model is requested
  expect: the decoded JSON has 2 entries in "components"
          and 3 entries in "requirements"

## BP-009-VIS-02: Top-level overview canvas

test TC-VIS-02-01 "Root path serves the canvas page"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-02
  given: the server is running
  when: GET / is requested
  expect: status 200 and the response body is an HTML
          document that loads the canvas application

## BP-009-VIS-03: Component detail pane on click

test TC-VIS-03-01 "Clicking a component opens the detail pane"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-03
  given: the top-level canvas is displayed with at least
         one component node
  when: the user clicks that component node
  expect: a detail pane is visible alongside the canvas
          and its header shows the clicked component's
          id and name

test TC-VIS-03-02 "Clicking the canvas background closes the pane"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-03
  given: the detail pane is open for some component
  when: the user clicks an empty area of the top canvas
  expect: the detail pane is closed

## BP-009-VIS-04: Detail pane toggles list and canvas views

test TC-VIS-04-01 "List view is the default representation"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-04
  given: the user has just opened the detail pane for a
         component
  expect: the pane initially displays the list view

test TC-VIS-04-02 "Toggle switches to canvas view"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-04
  given: the detail pane is showing the list view
  when: the user activates the canvas toggle
  expect: the pane displays the canvas view for the
          same component without closing the pane

## BP-009-VIS-05: List view groups derived reqs with test specs

test TC-VIS-05-01 "Derived reqs render with their testspecs nested"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-05
  given: the detail pane is showing the list view for a
         component that has derived requirements, each
         with at least one verifying test spec
  expect: each derived requirement is rendered with its
          verifying test specs visually grouped below it

test TC-VIS-05-02 "Component with no derived reqs shows empty state"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-05
  given: a component with no derived requirements
  when: the user opens its detail pane in list view
  expect: the list view renders an empty-state message
          instead of an empty section

## BP-009-VIS-06: Canvas view shows component local subgraph

test TC-VIS-06-01 "Canvas view includes the component and its neighbors"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-06
  given: the detail pane is toggled to canvas view for a
         component that has derived reqs, satisfied sysreqs,
         and verifying test specs
  expect: the sub-canvas renders nodes for the component,
          its derived requirements, its verifying test
          specs, and the system requirements it satisfies

## BP-009-VIS-07: Source file and line visible for elements

test TC-VIS-07-01 "Source path and line appear for selected element"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-07
  given: the detail pane is showing any element (component,
         requirement, or test spec)
  expect: the element's source_file path and line_number
          are visible in the pane

## BP-009-VIS-08: Single-port local server

test TC-VIS-08-01 "Server binds and serves on the configured port"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-08
  given: the server is instructed to listen on a free port
  when: the server is started
  expect: the server accepts GET /api/model on that port
          and returns the JSON model

test TC-VIS-08-02 "Default port is 8080"
  verifies: BP-009-VIS-08
  given: Serve is invoked with no port override
  when: the server is initialised
  expect: the listen address resolves to :8080
